All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:

**Bug:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// BEFORE (buggy) — loop exits one index short of the end
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// AFTER (fixed) — loop covers every element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` caused the loop to stop before the last element. For a 3-item array it only processed indices 0 and 1; for a single-item array the condition `i < 0` meant it never ran at all. Removing `- 1` fixes all three previously failing tests:

- ✅ `should process all items in the array` — now returns `["HELLO", "WORLD", "FOO"]`
- ✅ `should handle a single item` — now returns `["TEST"]`
- ✅ `should handle two items` — now returns `["A", "B"]`

